1. What Information Do We Collect?
Personal Information You Provide
We collect information you voluntarily provide when you:
Express interest in our Services
Register or interact with the app
Contact us directly
Examples of collected personal information:
Name
Email address
Contact or authentication data
Application Data
If you use our app, we may request access to:
Device sensors (e.g. step counter)
Push notifications
You can change app permissions at any time in your device settings.
⚠️ You must ensure that all provided information is true, accurate, and up to date.
2. How Do We Process Your Information?
We process your personal information to:
Provide, maintain, and improve our Services
Communicate with you
Prevent fraud and ensure security
Comply with legal obligations
Analyze app usage for internal reporting
With your consent, we may process your information for other specific purposes.
3. When and With Whom Do We Share Your Information?
We may share your personal information:
During business transfers: such as mergers, sales, or acquisitions
With business partners: to offer products, discounts, or promotions
4. How Long Do We Keep Your Information?
We retain personal information only as long as necessary for the purposes stated in this policy or as required by law.
When data is no longer needed:

We delete or anonymize it, or
Securely store and isolate it if deletion isn't possible immediately (e.g., backups)
5. What Are Your Privacy Rights?
Depending on your location, you may have the right to:
Access your personal data
Correct or update inaccurate data
Delete your personal data
Withdraw your consent at any time
To exercise these rights, contact us at lnarsia12@gmail.com.
⚠️ Withdrawing consent won’t affect past lawful processing.
6. Controls for Do-Not-Track (DNT) Features
Currently, we do not respond to DNT signals due to the absence of a uniform standard. If such a standard is adopted in the future, we will update our policy accordingly.
7. Do We Make Updates to This Notice?
Yes. We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Updates will be reflected by the “Last Updated” date.
For significant changes, we may:
Post an update prominently, or
Notify you directly
We encourage regular review of this notice.
8. How Can You Contact Us?
Email: lnarsia12@gmail.com
Mailing Address:
Bolta
Georgia
9. How Can You Review, Update, or Delete Your Data?
You can request to:
Access the personal data we’ve collected about you
Correct or delete your information
Withdraw your consent
Submit a Data Subject Access Request by contacting us at lnarsia12@gmail.com.
